7 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
8 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
9 Article – Public Utilities
10 2–110.
11 (a) In this section, “public service company” includes an electricity supplier and a
12 gas supplier as those terms are defined in § 1–101 of this article.
13 (b) (1) The costs and expenses of the Commission, the Strategic Energy
14 Planning Office, and the Office of People’s Counsel shall be borne by the public service
15 companies that are subject to the Commission’s jurisdiction.
16 (2) The costs and expenses shall be assessed as provided in this section.
17 (3) The Commission shall pay the money that it collects for the assessment
18 under this section into the Public Utility Regulation Fund in the State Treasury established
19 under § 2–110.1 of this subtitle to reimburse the State for the expenses of the Commission,
20 the Strategic Energy Planning Office, and the Office of People’s Counsel.
21 (c) (12) The total amount that may be charged to a public service company
22 under this section for a State fiscal year may not exceed:
23 (i) [0.50%] 0.25% of the public service company’s gross operating
24 revenues derived from intrastate utility and electricity supplier operations in the preceding
25 calendar year, or other 12–month period that the Chairman determines, for the costs and
26 expenses of the Commission other than that of the Strategic Energy Planning Office and
27 the Office of People’s Counsel; plus
28 (ii) 0.074% of those revenues for the costs and expenses of the
29 Strategic Energy Planning Office; plus
30 (iii) 0.074% of those revenues for the costs and expenses of the Office
31 of People’s Counsel.
32 7–316.

SENATE BILL 997 3
1 (a) In this section, “marketing” does not include materials to educate or inform,
2 IN A NEUTRAL MANNER, a retail customer about standard offer service, default gas
3 commodity service, or customer choice.
4 (b) Except as provided in subsection (d) of this section, an electric company or a
5 gas company may not recover through its rates any costs associated with marketing its
6 services.
7 (c) An electric cooperative may recover through its rates any costs associated with
8 marketing its services, including the costs associated with materials that educate or inform,
9 IN A NEUTRAL MANNER, a retail customer about standard offer service or customer choice.
10 (d) The Commission may, by regulation, adopt criteria for reviewing marketing
11 and other communication materials of an electric company or a gas company to determine
12 whether the cost of the materials may be recovered through the company’s rates.
13 7–507.
